This needs more detail, obviously.

* download nethack-331.tgz from nethack.org or some mirror.

* apply the patch
enh-331.patch

* configure it and build it
Read the Install file in the nethack tree.

Select LISP everywhere that is appropriate.

* byte-compile and install the emacs lisp code
make, and copy the .elc files somewhere into the load-path

* start emacs

* (require 'nethack)
or do some autoload magic

* M-x nethack RET
and 'hack away.
